title._content: Buchanan extended family enjoying 'high tea' outside the Clyde Hotel, Gympie Road, Strathpine

description._content: Photographer: Unidentified Location: Strathpine, Queensland, Australia Date: ca 1894 Description: From the left: Janet Buchanan (1870-1895); Mary Buchanan, later Day (1875-1938); James Mains Crawford (1810-1905); Catherine (Kate) Crawford, nee Buchanan (1868-1932); James Buchanan, Jr. (1866-1922); James Buchanan Sr. (1823-1906); Frederick Charles Hosier (1858-1897); Margaret (Mag) Hosier, nee Buchanan (1864-1945) James Sr. opened the Clyde Hotel in Strathpine in August 1874, continuing as the licensee until 1901. The Clyde Hotel stood on the site of today's Four Mile Creek Hotel.
